The paper deals with the problem of online compression of data streams in resource-constrained sensor networks. This problem involves aspects of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) as the authors propose algorithms for compressing data streams with quality guarantees. The paper also deals with networking and communication issues (cs.NI) as it addresses the problem of limited communication bandwidth in sensor networks. The development of optimal algorithms for data compression involves aspects of control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
